# Continuation Guide

## Multi-Session Continuity

- Agent transcripts: `C:\Users\rindo\.cursor\projects\c-dev-chili-home-copilot\agent-transcripts\`
- Search transcripts with Grep for keywords (task names, files, errors) to reconstruct context
- Check `.cursor/plans/*.plan.md` for existing plans before starting new work
- Check TodoWrite state for pending items from previous sessions
- Read the conversation summary carefully before acting

## Windows / PowerShell

- Use `;` to chain commands (not `&&`)
- `conda activate chili-env` before Python commands
- `rg` may not be installed — use the Grep tool instead
- Double-quote paths with spaces

## Large File Strategy

- `learning.py` (8k+ lines), `scanner.py` (4.7k+), `backtest_service.py` (2.1k+) — never read whole files
- Use Grep to find function definitions, then Read with offset/limit
- Key functions in `learning.py`: `run_learning_cycle`, `mine_patterns`, `mine_intraday_patterns`, `evolve_pattern_strategies`, `get_brain_stats`, `ensure_mined_scan_pattern`

## Migration Numbering

- Check LAST entry in `app/migrations.py::MIGRATIONS` before adding
- Current tail: `("069_supporting_tables", _migration_069_supporting_tables)`
- Next: `070_*`. Never skip numbers.
- Pattern: define `_migration_NNN_name(conn)`, append tuple to MIGRATIONS

## LLM Integration

- Use `from ..llm_caller import call_llm` in services (avoids circular imports)
- Trading brain LLM usage: cycle reports (`learning_cycle_report.py`), journal (`journal.py`), brain assistant (`brain_assistant.py`), web research (`web_pattern_researcher.py`)
- Prompts in `app/prompts/*.txt` — don't hardcode in Python
- Always fallback when LLM calls fail

